<div lang="en" dir="ltr" class="mw-content-ltr">
'''Lunar New Year 2026''' was a limited-time [[Special:MyLanguage/Shop|Shop]] promotion by [[Special:MyLanguage/VRChat|VRChat]], tied to the [[wikipedia:Lunar New Year|Lunar New Year]] and the Year of the Horse.<ref name="yt-lny">[https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=R3NCRAneZ_g "Lunar New Year 2026 VRChat Shop Update"] on ''[https://youtube.com/@VRChat YouTube]''. Dated February 17, 2026. Retrieved April 9, 2026.</ref><ref name="devupdate">[https://ask.vrchat.com/t/developer-update-19-february-2026 "Developer Update - 19 February 2026"] on ''[https://ask.vrchat.com ask.vrchat.com]''. Dated February 19, 2026. Retrieved April 9, 2026.</ref> It added a themed shelf of [[Special:MyLanguage/Items|items]], [[Special:MyLanguage/Portals|portals]], a warp effect, stickers, and emojis. A free [[Special:MyLanguage/VRC+|VRC+]]-exclusive credit bundle styled as a "Lucky Red Envelope" was also part of the promotion. It was the first Lunar New Year promotion in VRChat to include purchasable Shop items; the previous year's celebration in early 2025 (Year of the Snake) had offered only a free limited-time [[Special:MyLanguage/Stickers|sticker]] set.<ref name="stickers-wiki">[https://wiki.vrchat.com/wiki/Stickers "Stickers"] on ''VRChat Wiki''. Retrieved April 9, 2026.</ref>
</div>

<div lang="en" dir="ltr" class="mw-content-ltr">
== Overview ==
</div>

<div lang="en" dir="ltr" class="mw-content-ltr">
The promotion marked the Year of the Horse with new Shop content.<ref name="yt-lny"/> Themed listings on the Lunar New Year shelf ran from February 17, 2026 through April 1, 2026, with lower prices on paid items for VRC+ subscribers. The February 17, 2026 YouTube video "honse update | VRChat Shop Refresh!" presented the Shop update,<ref name="yt-lny"/> and the February 19, 2026 Developer Update on [https://ask.vrchat.com ask.vrchat.com] covering the promotion.<ref name="devupdate"/>
</div>

<div lang="en" dir="ltr" class="mw-content-ltr">
The video ran about one minute 23 seconds, showed each item in the promotion, and featured LazyTheDinoKing and InviaWaffles.<ref name="yt-lny"/> Its description listed the drop as including "a new Portal, Warp Effect, Premium Emoji's, Premium Stickers and 3 new items: Lucky Coin, Firecrackers & Pallet Drum."<ref name="yt-lny"/>
</div>

<div lang="en" dir="ltr" class="mw-content-ltr">
The '''Lucky Red Envelope''' was later offered on its own as a free Shop redemption for VRC+ subscribers for a limited time,<ref name="bsky-feb19">VRChat (@vrchat.com), [https://bsky.app/profile/vrchat.com Bluesky], posts dated February 19, 2026. Retrieved April 9, 2026.</ref> granting {{Credits|399}}. The same day, VRChat's [[wikipedia:Threads (social network)|Threads]] account posted about the envelope.<ref name="threads-lre">[https://www.threads.com/@officialvrchat/post/DU62IqUjmKP VRChat (@officialvrchat)], Threads, post dated February 19, 2026. Retrieved April 9, 2026.</ref>
</div>

<div lang="en" dir="ltr" class="mw-content-ltr">
The envelope was first set to grant {{Credits|400}}, but the reward was changed to {{Credits|399}} before broader availability. The reduction reflected [[wikipedia:Tetraphobia|tetraphobia]]: in some East Asian cultures the word for "four" sounds like the word for "death."<ref name="strasz-399">[https://ask.vrchat.com/t/developer-update-19-february-2026/47849/34 strasz, reply in "Developer Update - 19 February 2026"] on ''[https://ask.vrchat.com ask.vrchat.com]''. Retrieved April 9, 2026.</ref> Some users who redeemed on February 19, 2026, before the change, received {{Credits|400}} instead of 399.<ref name="feedback-bug">[https://feedback.vrchat.com/bug-reports/p/unable-to-claim-additional-399-promo-credits-as-a-vrc-subscriber-received-400-pr "Unable to claim 399 promo credits as a VRC+ subscriber, received 400 promo credits instead of 399 credits earlier (Lucky Red Envelope)"] on ''VRChat Feedback''. Retrieved April 9, 2026.</ref> Per Shop listing data, the Lucky Red Envelope was listed from February 18, 2026 through April 1, 2026.
</div>

